GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
H 1
HOUSE BILL 294
Short Title: Jackson Co Bd of Ed Election Partisan. (Local)
Sponsors: Representative Clampitt.
For a complete list of sponsors, refer to the North Carolina General Assembly web site.
Referred to: Election Law, if favorable, Rules, Calendar, and Operations of the House
March 6, 2025
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO PROVIDE FOR THE PARTISAN ELECTION OF MEMBERS OF THE
3 JACKSON COUNTY BOARD OF EDUCATION AND TO MAKE OTHER TECHNICAL
4 CHANGES.
5 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
6 SECTION 1.(a) Section 5(a) of S.L. 2024-14 reads as rewritten:
7 "SECTION 5.(a) The Jackson County Board of Education shall consist of five members
8 elected from five single-member residency districts to serve staggered four-year terms. One
9 member shall be elected from each residency district by the qualified voters of the entire county.
10 Elections for the Jackson County Board of Education shall be held in even-numbered years at the
11 time of the general election with results determined by the nonpartisan plurality method in
12 accordance with G.S. 163-292. on a partisan basis as provided in G.S. 163-291 as terms expire.
13 Candidates for election to the board of education shall be nominated at the same time and manner
14 as other county officers. Members shall take office on the first Monday in December following
15 the election. Members shall serve until a successor has been elected and qualified. Except as
16 otherwise provided by this section, the election shall be conducted in accordance with the
17 applicable provisions of Chapter 115C and 163 of the General Statutes. All vacancies on the
18 Jackson County Board of Education shall be filled in accordance with G.S. 115C-37.1."
19 SECTION 1.(b) This section becomes effective December 1, 2025.
20 SECTION 2.(a) Section 5(f) of S.L. 2024-14 reads as rewritten:
21 "SECTION 5.(f) This section is effective the first Monday in December 2026, 2025, and the
22 2026 2025 elections and elections thereafter shall be conducted accordingly."
23 SECTION 2.(b) G.S. 115C-37.1(d) reads as rewritten:
24 "(d) This section shall apply only to the Hickory City Board of Education and the
25 Newton-Conover City Board of Education and in the following counties: Alleghany, Ashe,
26 Beaufort, Brunswick, Burke, Cabarrus, Caldwell, Carteret, Catawba, Cherokee, Clay, Craven,
27 Dare, Davie, Forsyth, Graham, Harnett, Henderson, Hyde, Iredell, Jackson, Lee, Lincoln,
28 Madison, McDowell, Mitchell, New Hanover, Onslow, Pamlico, Pender, Polk, Rutherford,
29 Stanly, Stokes, Surry, Vance, Washington, and Yancey."
30 SECTION 2.(c) This section becomes effective December 1, 2025.
31 SECTION 3. Except as otherwise provided, this act is effective when it becomes law
32 and applies to elections occurring on or after that date.
*H294-v-1*

